📌 Project Overview

This project predicts medical insurance charges based on user information such as age, gender, BMI, number of children, smoking status, and other factors.

A Machine Learning model is trained using Linear Regression to estimate insurance costs.

🚀 Features
Data loading and preprocessing
Exploratory data analysis
Feature selection
Train-test data splitting
Linear Regression model training
Model evaluation using R² score
Insurance charge prediction
🛠️ Technologies Used
Python
Pandas
NumPy
Matplotlib
Seaborn
Scikit-learn
Jupyter Notebook
📂 Dataset

The dataset contains information about insurance customers:

Feature	Description
age	Age of the customer
sex	Gender of customer
bmi	Body Mass Index
children	Number of children
smoker	Smoking status
charges	Medical insurance cost
⚙️ Machine Learning Workflow
Import required libraries
Load the insurance dataset
Analyze and preprocess the data
Split data into training and testing sets
Train Linear Regression model
Predict insurance charges
Evaluate model performance
📊 Model

Algorithm used:

Linear Regression

The model learns the relationship between customer attributes and insurance charges.

📈 Model Evaluation

The model is evaluated using:

R² Score (Coefficient of Determination)

Example:

model.score(X_test, y_test)
▶️ How to Run
Clone the repository:
git clone <repository-url>
Install dependencies:
pip install pandas numpy matplotlib seaborn scikit-learn
Open the notebook:
jupyter notebook project_insurance.ipynb
Run all cells.
